Peptidase_M20 Involved in the anaerobic nitrogen utilization via the assimilation of allantoin. Catalyzes specifically the hydrolysis of allantoate to yield CO2, NH3 and S-ureidoglycine, which is unstable and readily undergoes a second deamination by S-ureidoglycine aminohydrolase AllE to yield S-ureidoglycolate and NH3. In vivo, the spontaneous release of S-ureidoglycolate and ammonia from S- ureidoglycine appears to be too slow to sustain an efficient flux of nitrogen

Ldh_2 AllD plays a pivotal role as a metabolic branch-point enzyme in nitrogen utilization via the assimilation of allantoin. It is able to utilize allantoin as a sole source of nitrogen under anaerobic conditions. Catalyzes the oxidation of ureidoglycolate to oxalurate
